Foot-and-mouth disease, Lebanon
-------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 19 Apr 2007 from Dr Georges
Phrerm, Acting Director of Animal Resources, Animal Resources
Directorate:, Ministry of Agriculture, Beyrouth, Lebanon
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 7 Feb 2007
Date of confirmation of event: !5 Feb 2007
Report date: 19 Apr 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 19 Apr 2007
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2003
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: FMD virus, serotype pending
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (basic)
Report pertains to: entire country
New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Hasbaya, Al Janoub
Date of start of outbreak: 25 Feb 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species: sheep/goats
Susceptible: 350
Cases: 65
Deaths: 4
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: routine vaccination is not applied in sheep and
goats in this region.
Outbreak 2: Zahle suburb, Al Biqa
Date of start of outbreak: 7 Feb 2007
Outbreak status: resolved (10 Mar 2007)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species: cattle
Susceptible: 70
Cases: 4
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: dairy cattle; sheep and goats in this area but
without clinical signs (vaccinated with an O serotype vaccine).
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Outbreak statistics
Species: sheep/goats
Apparent morbidity rate:18.57 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 1.14 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 6.15 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 1.14 percent
Species: cattle
Apparent morbidity rate: 5.71 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 0 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 0 percent
Proportion susceptible removed*: 0 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: illegal movement of animals
Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Fanar Laboratory, Lebanese Agricultural
Research Institute (LARI) (National laboratory)
Species: cattle
Test: antibody detection ELISA (enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay)
Test date: 15 Feb 2007
Result: positive
--
